Overview

[Job 10:1](../../../bib/kjv/job010.htm#001.md), Job, taking liberty of
complaint, expostulates with God about his afflictions; [Job
10:18](../../../bib/kjv/job010.htm#018.md), He complains of life, and
craves a little ease before death.

